Text: The process starts when the SO: Angebot/Auftrag receives a subsidiary order.
The SO: Angebot/Auftrag prepares goods for shipment and then ships the goods, concurrently with preparing the goods and shipping them, the SO: Angebot/Auftrag prepares invoicing.
Constraints extracted: [PRECEDENCE(A=prepare good for shipment, B=prepare good), PRECEDENCE(A=prepare good for shipment, B=ship them)]

Text: In case the customer is subsidiary and the subsidiary relationship is not yet modeled, SO: Address- management adds parent company as invoicing address, then the SO: Angebot/Auftrag create the invoice.
Constraints extracted: [PRECEDENCE(A=model subsidiary relationship, B=add parent company), PRECEDENCE(A=model subsidiary relationship, B=invoice address), PRECEDENCE(A=model subsidiary relationship, B=create invoice)]

Text: Otherwise if the customer is independent or the subsidiary relationship is already modeled in ERP, the SO: Angebot/Auftrag directly creates the invoice.
Constraints extracted: [EXISTENCE(A=the customer is independent or the subsidiary relationship is already modeled in ERP , the SO : Angebot / Auftrag directly creates the invoice . )]

Text: Finally, the SO: Angebot/Auftrag sends the invoice.
